MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
In order to qualify for this position your resume must provide sufficient experience and/or education, knowledge, skills, and abilities to perform the duties of the specific position for which you are being considered. Your resume is the key means we have for evaluating your skills, knowledge, and abilities as they relate to this position. Therefore, we encourage you to be clear and specific when describing your experience. Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-05 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: -Receiving, reviewing and analyzing purchase request from various departments for and operational supplies, equipment and services; -Processing routine, urgent, and emergency needed materials in vastly different commodity groups, classes and services on the open market using Purchase Card Programs, Blanket Purchase Agreements, Purchase Delivery orders and similar items;
-Soliciting quotations through telephone contacts, email, or written request for quotation (RFQ);
-Administering all purchases and certifying invoices for credit card buys, blanket purchases agreements, purchase orders, and delivery orders. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website:
https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series
https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=GS-CLER Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.

Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-06 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: 1) Knowledge of purchasing regulations, policies, procedures, and business practices in obtaining oral and written quotations for goods and services; 2) Issuing purchase orders for a wide variety of items;
3) Resolving or recommending solutions to problems (i.e. delays or damage to goods in shipment, poor quality or workmanship, substitutions, etc.).; 4) Reviewing purchase request to ensure they are meet standards of Government Purchase Card program; 5) Skill in analyzing descriptions provided by customers to determine if specifications or work statements are adequate; and 6) Maintains records for accountability of procured supplies, equipment and services. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website:
